Description: Fragment of handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay fine light brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47). Name Eukleitos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0350.10.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0937)
